{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17631658","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17631658"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:30:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:30:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17388"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17388","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17388"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10078"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75487"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10078","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10078"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17388"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60997"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"7722"},{"type":"tags","id":"7726"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23586"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23594"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75487","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75487"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe scatter plot below shows systolic blood pressure measurements plotted against age for ten women attending a primary care clinic (Image).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the relationship between age and systolic blood pressure demonstrated in this scatter plot?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Strong negative correlation","Moderate positive correlation","Perfect negative correlation","Perfect positive correlation","No correlation"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe scatter plot shows a \u003Cstrong\u003Emoderate positive correlation\u003C/strong\u003E between age and systolic blood pressure. As age increases, blood pressure tends to increase, but there is some scatter around the trend line indicating the relationship is not perfect.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect interpretations can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPerfect positive correlation\u003C/strong\u003E would show all points falling exactly on a straight line with positive slope\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStrong negative correlation\u003C/strong\u003E would show points trending downward from left to right\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENo correlation\u003C/strong\u003E would show points scattered randomly with no clear pattern\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPerfect negative correlation\u003C/strong\u003E would show all points falling exactly on a straight line with negative slope\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EScatter plots are useful for visualising relationships between continuous variables and can help identify patterns, outliers, and the strength and direction of associations in the data.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["A scatter plot shows the relationship between two continuous variables by plotting individual data points on an x-y coordinate system.","A moderate positive correlation shows data points trending upward with some scatter around the trend line.","Blood pressure tends to increase with age in women, showing a moderate positive correlation."],"references":["Sullivan LM. Essentials of biostatistics in public health. 3rd ed. Burlington (MA): Jones \u0026 Bartlett Learning; 2018.","Dawson B, Trapp RG. Basic \u0026 clinical biostatistics